SIMPLE: pshaw
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pshaw
<hw>Pshaw</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>interj.</pos> <ety>[Of imitative
origin.]</ety> <def>Pish! pooch! -- an exclamation used as an expression
of contempt, disdain, dislike, etc.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>psha</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pshaw</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pshaw
<hw>Pshaw</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To express disgust or
contemptuous disapprobation, as by the exclamation ⟦ldquo⟧
<xex>Pshaw</xex>!⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The goodman used regularly to frown and <qex>pshaw</qex> wherever
this topic was touched upon.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Psilanthropic</ent>⟦br⟧
